==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[Babylon#Latin|Babylōn]], from Greek [[Βαβυλών]], from Hebrew [[בבל]] (English [[Babel]]), from Akkadian ''bāb ili'' ‘gate of God’; the name of the ancient Chaldean capital and Biblical city of the Apocalypse.

===Proper noun===
'''Babylon'''

# Capital of [[Babylonia]] in the 2nd and 1st century BC.
# Any city of great wealth,luxury and vice.
# (''Rastafarianism'') Term for the so-called white man's civilization.

